@pipermerriam this was already approved a while back but it didn't fully work back then and I made substantial changes now to get it working.

This has one commit from #1212 cherry-picked (so that will fall out of that other PR if we merge this first), which is the one that brings in isolated plugins and sets up the eventbus architecture. While isolated plugins aren't used in this PR, the event bus structure is used to propagate a `ShutdownRequest` back to the main process where the shutdown is then handled.

This works reasonable well. There *is* room for improvement because it can happen that the db process shuts down while the networking process is trying to connect to it and then we are left with an ugly unhandled exception but other than that, it shuts down smoothly. Getting rid of that error would take a bit of rethinking the node boot process I guess. However, imho, we don't need to address this now. This works reasonable well from my point of view.

